classes^#^
SUBTOPIC-player^#^
		-=[ Classes ]=-

  There are four main classes within the Heaven7 Mudlib. Each player
may obtain any number or combination of these, to a maximum of three
classes in all. 
  The classes available are:

  1) Mage - Wizards who gather their power from 8 schools of magic.

  2) Cleric - Servants of the Gods whose power is granted through
     prayer and the spreading of the word of their faith. 

  3) Fighter - Fighters are warriors, guards, and hired mercenaries.
     Their strength comes from their skills of weaponry and armour.

  4) Thief - Thieves are skilled in stealth, lock skills, and the
     art of skullduggery. 

  Only certain races have the necesary skills to be trained in some 
classes. Dwarves and halflings are innately magic resistant, hence
the study of magic is never to their advantage. Such races can not
learn magic. Others are simply not intelligent enough, like the ogre,
and giant kindred.

  When you leave a class you must return to the place where you train.
If you have an excessive amount of experience points still remaining
your spendable experience points will be capped. This is to prevent
players from using exp gained in one class spending it on a new one
in which they have yet received no exp.

  Note that all skills in the class you wish to leave will no longer
be accessable, and hence set to zero. This is not done for realism but
for overall game balance.




  For more help, see also 'help <class>', and the manuals for classes.

  See also: help <class>
            help subclass

