channel^#^
SUBTOPIC-player^#^
		-=[ Channel Help ]=-


		Usage: channel <channel>
	      Command: channel

	  Description: The channel function is designed to allow
		       players a chat/channel system for communication
		       and discussion of various topics OOC (out of 
                       character).

		       There are several channels, including:
		       OOC - Out of character discussion 
		       wiz - Wizards channel only.
		       lpc - Wizards discussion for lpc.

	E.g. 'channel ooc' 
	This will turn you onto the ooc channel. By typing it again
	it will disable this channel.
        When you type 'ooc <message', everyone listenning to the OOC
        channel will hear you. By default, all players are listenning
        to the OOC line.

        Other commands: <channel> <who>
                E.g.  : ooc who
         Description  : Shows who is listenning to the <channel> channel.
        
        Other commands: <channel> -h
                E.g.  : ooc -h
         Description  : Shows you the last few messages on that channel.

